==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Half-hearted
<hw>Half"-heart`ed</hw></mhw>
<pr>(-h⟦aum⟧rt`⟦ecr⟧d)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Wanting in
heart or spirit; ungenerous; unkind.</def> <rj><au>B.
Jonson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Lacking zeal or courage; performed with less than a
full effort; lukewarm; unenthusiastic; <as>as, a <ex>half-hearted</ex>
attempt</as>; -- of actions.</def> <wns>[wns=1]</wns> <rj><au>H.
James.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>half-holiday</ent>⟦br⟧
